At 08:24 6/28/2002 -0600, Barkes, Tara wrote:
>Hello everyone.
>My friend has a '78 automatic fuel injected bus.  It just recently had a
>tune up and all the seals have been replaced.  For some reason that we just
>haven't figured out is that it quits every time it gets warmed up.
===================>
Fuel
Air
Spark

Start with the most obvious, and work towards the less likely.

My order of inspection would be:
Check for spark immediately when it acts up, and before it cools down.
Then go to a fuel flow check.
The go to and air check.
